### Test Horizon-HCM Auth Integration
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "test@horizon-hcm.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!",
  "name": "Test User"
}

### 2. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "test@horizon-hcm.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

### 3. Get current user (requires auth token from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Enable 2FA
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/2fa/enable
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 5. Get 2FA QR Code
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/2fa/qr
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. List devices
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/devices
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Register push token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/push/register
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "token": "expo-push-token-here",
  "platform": "ios"
}

### 8. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
